notesStmt.note: Printed edition is cataloged separately under the title Pub. Terentij comici nobilissimi sex: q[uae] exta[n]t: fabul[ae].

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Printed edition of the comedies of Terence (Pub[lii] Terentii comici nobilissimi sex q[uae] exta[n]t fabule ..., Leipzig: Melchior Lotters, 1512) with extensive interlinear and marginal annotations, including summaries of each scene. Numerous marginal notes damaged by trimming.
msContents.textLang: Latin, with a few notes in German

msItem.title: Title page and biography of Terence, f. 1r

supportDesc.extent: 108 leaves : 278 x 190 mm. bound to 285 x 211 mm

collation.p: Paper, 108; 1-18⁶; gatherings have printed signatures A-I, K-S; [1-108], modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Annotations written in Gothic cursive with some notes in a calligraphic script, in multiple hands.

decoDesc.decoNote: Underlining of short passages of printed text in red, green, or blue ink in a section from the end of Eunuchus into the beginning of Adelphi (f. 38r-57r); marginal notes in red ink in Eunuchus (f. 25r-35v); initials touched with red on one page (f. 38v) ; various manicules throughout.

origin.p: Probably written in Leipzig, soon after the publication of the printed work in June 1512 (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Jean Jules Olinger (armorial bookplate inside upper cover).
Transferred from Culture Class collection, University of Pennsylvania, 2012.
